sean@sdg.dra.com (Sean Donelan) writes:

>The same could also be said of copyright, although the deposit requirements
>keep getting weakened.

As far as I know there are no deposit requirements at all. a work is automatically
copyrighted as soon as it is produced. Depositing it may help you establishing your 
claim that you actually did write the work, but it is not necessary. Anyone have different
information?
